rComments: I thank the professor very much for all the support efforts that he made for me during the semester.
The best course to learn legal theory and understand the phenomena of legal pluralism in the 21st century.

Lectures are very dry. He would post all his slides onto Brightspace after the lectures, so showing up to class was almost useless: just watch for pop quizzes at the end of class. For the final, you pick either a 20-page essay with 70 scholarly references from 2019 or sooner (??) or an oral presentation on one case law. Wouldn't recommend this prof
This course allows learning a lot about theories of law and their roles in judicial decisions.

It has been an absolute pleasure learning from this online course of conflict resolution. Professor was always available for online appointments.

Possibly the worst professor I have had. Le cours est quand même facile. L'analyse d'arrêt est difficile surtout si on a pas de background en droit. Le prof est parfois monotone dans son cours mais il est super gentil et tient réellement au succès de ses étudiants. Il connait très bien sa matière et est très respectable.

Pro OVALLE is critical of the system, and we learn it from his case law analyse tools. It is a lot reading for each case law, but it is a good investment if you are interested in the admission at the law programme.
A hard work is needed in this course, but you learn a lot regarding social justice for vulnerable people as well as you can get a good mark.

honestly, not worth the headache, he doesn't know how to teach and does the same crap every single year, every single class you have the choice to either do a coop of 35 hours or a presentation on some law article legit EVERY SINGLE YEAR! waste of time. and then every class he does a quizz online and it's on 3 points and the final is 160 questions.

Vraiment bon prof. Une dizaine de petit quiz (un à la fin de chaque cours), un examen de mi-session (choix multiples, courtes définitions et une question à long développement), une analyse d'arrêt et un travail de recherche. Passionné, communique bien sa matière et clair par rapport aux exigences. Un cours très intéressant qui fait réfléchir.
Professor Ovalle is tech guy, who teaches using easy online quizzes, it suffices to read the docs and to listen to him; he preaches for a modern legal theory of law.
Professor OVALLE DIAZ explain law for beginners, particularly, how law operates in social sciences field. Now, I am in Law school.

Ses PP sont chargés et parfois on le perd un peu quand il parle, mais si on l'écoute, ses cours sont très intéressants.

Legal pluralism is his topic. He is the only professor who ca explain you how the "non-states" actors create legal rules. This course is not helpful for the bar exam, but you get a very good understanding of the situation regarding the future of the lawyers job.
He is very professor, because he gives a lot of practical examples. However, his exams are very heavy for the level of this course. Additionally, he gives you to much reading to do for the semester.
